args: Fasten that last pesky strap, and...done!\nI've truly outdone myself, I must say.
At long last, my darling and I can embark\non a (swim)suitably steamy seaside tryst!
He's going to be smitten, charmed,\nAND enraptured, mark my words.
Mym, what say you we take a walk?\nJust the two of us. I want you in that\nswimsuit all to myself.
Oh, to dream. He would never say\nsomething like that.
I mean, sure, we've gotten closer, but...
You really know how to spoil a girl rotten,\ndarling. I'm so happy to be spending time\ntogether like this.
My pleasure. After all, you always do so\nmuch for us.
What? Say, darling...how exactly do you\nfeel about me?
I value you as a dear comrade, of course.
That's not what I mean! I'll ask you\nstraight-out, then. Do you like me?
Oh, I just KNEW you did!\nThat's why you're here on this date—
And Elisanne and Ranzal...and everyone in\nthe Halidom. You're all wonderful people.
My darling is even more thick-headed in\nromance than I am, and I'm a DRAGON.
Despite all I do to get his attention,\nit's like he's not even seeing me that\nway at all... Confidence...depleting...
Luckily for me, I've got a hydrodynamic\ntrump card up my sleeve. He's going to\ndo a TRIPLE-take when he sees this fit!
There's even a perfect event to set the\nmood happening on the beach. Jackpot.
Let's see. According to the pamphlet I\ngot from the cafe...
＂At some point, crystals containing sea\nbreeze mana took on the moniker of\n'wishing crystals.'＂
＂These desire-granting crystals float in\nthe air when wishes are made upon them.＂
OK, got that out of my system.\nI'm off to see my dar—
Whew. You okay?\n...Hey, wait, you're a faerie!
And you're...a dragon?\nI can't believe you saved me.
After that shriek of yours, how could I not?
I can't say I put ＂save a faerie in peril＂\non my bingo card for today. What brings\nyou here?
First, let me say thank you. I've come to\nthis beach to make a wishing crystal.
Oh, so we're here for the same reason.\nDidn't know faeries were into this too.
I created the event myself,\nso I would sure hope so.
Are you telling me this is all your doing?
Those are replicas humans made with sea\nbreeze crystals. They're just an imitation\nof the real ones that I create.

They only float because of the mana
they're made with. You don't actually have
to wish on them; you need only warm them
in your hand a little, and off they go.
Well, that's one illusion officially\nshattered. *sigh* So much for my dream.
No need to be so despondent.\nI want to collect strong wishes, you see...
And the wishing crystal is something\nI originally made in order to amplify\nfaerie power.
The more fervent the desire, the greater\nthe resultant energy. I collect that in the\ncrystals, and then make its power my own.
Ah. So that's why you put this event\ntogether—to bring supplicants in droves.
That's the idea. You're as sharp as you\nare strong.
You know what? I like you. You helped me\nout, so here. Let me give you a freshly\nmade crystal as thanks.
Not necessary. I'm a dragon, so I don't\nhave much use for a little trinket like that.
But weren't you just bemoaning the fact\nthat you have a dream going unfulfilled?
True, nothing will happen if you make a\nwish on a replica crystal...
But the real deal? That actually WILL grant\nyour heart's desire.
That's right. Now here, don't be shy!\nTake the darn thing already.
I'll be in this cave for a while, so come let\nme know when your wish gets granted.\nLooking forward to the good news!
Hey, wait! Sheesh... What a pushy faerie.
Well, I've got my little magic ticket here,\nso I may as well make use of it. I wish...
...that my darling would have eyes only\nfor me.
There's no way it could've been that easy.\n...Could it?
You know what, never mind.\nI have somewhere to be.
Aha, there they are. Hi, everyone!\nSorry to keep you all waaaiting!
You certainly took your time Mym.\nThe barbecue is already—ngh?!
Mym, run! Quickly! The sea is—
(Where'd a giant wave like this come\nfrom all of a sudden?! Ow ow ow...)
Mym! MYM! Are you all right?!
That enormous wave crashed ashore and\nnearly drowned you. I'm so relieved you're\nokay.
I see. Thank you for saving—
Wait. What's going on? Why is he...?
He ran into the water to save ya,\nand ended up goin' under too...
This is all my fault. I'm so sorry.\nPlease, my love, open your eyes!
Oh, what a relief! You're awake!
Sorry, uh... Who are you all again?
